description: Spotted from the Edmonds-Kingston ferry, near fishing boats.
From the Inn at Langley looking east there was a very large group of porpoise swimming south in the Saratoga passage
heading north in the Tacoma narrows,, between pt. evans and the entrance to gig harbor, saw its back and tail break the surface a couple times.

A large splash (breech?) first observed off Ketron Island at about 1345 hrs. Then at approximately 1400 hrs a smaller (adolecent?) Humpback (?) Whale was seen swimming North of Sunnyside Beach toward the Tacoma Narrows.
On train near picnic point (south of Mukilteo) saw 2 breaches half mile off shore, very large baleen whale. Unable to confirm humpback due to limited viewing do to being on a train.
Passing north close to shore at eagle point.  About three or four groups. 6 or 7 in the first group. Two  males. Some moms and babies.

Observed a whale maybe gray, not orca from bluff about 3 miles north of edmonds ferry. 3-4 miles directly west between pt. no pt. & north edmonds/meadowdale. Jumping out of water and slapping its tail. Moving south. The
